President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed October 28, 2023, as National First Responders Day in honor of the courageous and selfless sacrifice made by first responders across the United States. The article acknowledges the daily challenges faced by law enforcement officers, firefighters, emergency medical service providers, and other public health workers. President Biden highlights the importance of supporting and protecting first responders and mentions various initiatives and legislation aimed at providing resources, benefits, and improved working conditions for these heroes. The President expresses gratitude to first responders and emphasizes their commitment to serving their fellow Americans. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to observe National First Responders Day with appropriate programs, ceremonies, and activities to honor and pay tribute to these brave individuals.